## Superseded from resolve-blocked-todos

```markdown
---
name: resolve-blocked-todos
description: 'Resolve TODO markers blocked by a now-closed issue. Use when: (1) a
  tracking issue has TODO(#N) markers and issue #N is now closed, (2) disabled tests
  have TODO comments waiting on a dependency, (3) cleanup issues need to be resolved
  after a blocking PR merges.'
category: testing
date: 2026-03-05
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
---
## Overview

| Property | Value |
| ---------- | ------- |
| **Category** | testing |
| **Trigger** | Blocking issue closed; TODO(#N) markers remain in code |
| **Outcome** | All TODO markers removed, disabled tests enabled, functionality implemented |

## When to Use

- `gh issue view N --json state -q '.state'` returns `"CLOSED"` for the blocking issue
- Tests are commented out with TODO markers and the dependency is now resolved

## Verified Workflow

```bash
# Phase A: Verify blocking issue is closed
gh issue view <N> --json state -q '.state'   # must return "CLOSED"

# Phase B: Locate all TODO markers
grep -rn "TODO.*#<N>\|TODO(#<N>)" --include="*.mojo" .

# Phase C: Check for implementation on feature branch
git branch --all | grep "<N>"
git cherry-pick <commit-hash> --no-commit

# Phase G: Verify no TODO markers remain
grep -rn "TODO.*#<N>" --include="*.mojo" .
```

For each TODO: remove the comment, uncomment test code, replace `pass  # Placeholder`
with real assertions, add needed imports.

## Failed Attempts

| Attempt | What Was Tried | Why It Failed | Lesson Learned |
| --------- | ---------------- | --------------- | ---------------- |
| Assumed blocking issue was still open | Relied on tracking issue description "wait until #2722 resolves" | Issue had been closed since the tracking issue was created | Always verify `gh issue view N --json state` first |
| Waited for methods to appear in main | Expected `__str__`, `__repr__`, `__hash__` in current main branch | Implementation was on branch `2722-auto-impl`, not yet merged | Check git branches and cherry-pick from the feature branch |
| Use `contiguous(b)` as a module-level function | Test comments implied module-level function | Only `tensor.contiguous()` method and `as_contiguous()` function exist | Always verify function signatures with grep before enabling commented code |
```
